<h2>PhpStorm: Create structure of module</h2>
<p>It's very helpful to create module structure by one click.</p>

<p>We have to create bash script for it:</p>
<pre class="prettyprint linenums languague-bash">
#!/bin/sh
mkdir "$1"
echo "<?php" > "$1/$1.module"
echo "" >> "$1/$1.module"
echo "name = $1" > "$1/$1.info"
echo "core = 7.x" >> "$1/$1.info"
echo "version = '7.x-1.0'" >> "$1/$1.info"
</pre>

<p>Save this code to file, for example ~/bin/drupal_create_module.sh<br/>
And give permissions to run: <b>chmod +x ~/bin/drupal_create_module.sh</b></p>

<p>Go to <i>Preferences->External Tools</i> and just add new tool.</p>
